# Axodus Global Architecture

## Architectural Direction

Axodus evolves as a federated operating ecosystem composed of interoperable governance, treasury, execution, educational, AI, and financial domains.

The ecosystem is intentionally modular.

No workspace should become a monolith.

---

# Core Architecture Layers


Users
  ↓
Constitutional Governance Layer
  ↓
Local Governance Layer
  ↓
Constitutional Enforcement Layer
  ↓
Protocol Execution Layer
  ↓
Product Infrastructure Layer
  ↓
Cross-chain Coordination Layer
  ↓
AI Orchestration Layer

---

# Governance Layer

The governance layer is composed of two governance nuclei:

* Constitutional Governance
* Local Governance

Constitutional Governance is powered by `$Neurons`.

It defines federal standards, ecosystem capabilities, constitutional conditions, guardrails, and ecosystem-wide legitimacy.

Local Governance is controlled by each federated startup, DAO, company, product, or community.

Local Governance may use `$Neurons`, local tokens, auto-generated platform tokens, multisigs, gauges, reputation systems, NFT governance, or plugin-defined models.

Local autonomy is allowed, but every local governance model must remain constitutionally compatible.

The governance layer coordinates:

* DAOs
* federation records
* proposal lifecycle
* permissions
* execution authorization
* treasury policies
* constitutional enforcement
* Constitutional Guardrails with transparent reason codes

Governance is chain-agnostic.

Harmony is a supported adapter, not the canonical governance core.

Do not use opaque automatic exclusion language.

Restricted governance actions must be expressed as Constitutional Guardrails with explicit reason codes.

---

# Federation Model

Axodus uses a federated DAO architecture.

Each DAO:

* remains autonomous
* owns local permissions
* owns local treasury rights
* may join federations
* may share execution capabilities
* must remain constitutionally compatible

Federation membership never overrides explicit local governance permissions, and local permissions never bypass Constitutional Governance constraints.

---

# Chain Roles

## Execution Chains

Canonical governance and treasury authority.

## Voting Chains

Voting participation and governance power aggregation.

## Spoke Chains

Operational product execution and infrastructure hosting.

---

# Registry Philosophy

The registry layer is the ecosystem source of truth.

Registries define:

* chains
* deployments
* plugins
* capabilities
* permissions
* execution rights
* adapters
* treasury compatibility

Registries must support:

* on-chain verification
* off-chain indexing
* append-only metadata
* deterministic references

---

# Plugin Philosophy

Custom behavior belongs in:

* plugins
* setup processors
* adapters
* conditions

Avoid deep protocol forks whenever possible.

Preserve:

* upgradeability
* modularity
* governance transparency
* permission boundaries

---

# Treasury Philosophy

Treasury systems must:

* remain auditable
* expose execution receipts
* support governance routing
* support federation-aware execution
* preserve accounting integrity

No hidden operator authority is allowed.

---

# AI Orchestration Layer

AI systems are treated as operational tooling.

AI execution must:

* remain bounded
* remain permissioned
* remain auditable
* expose execution logs
* support governance review

AI systems must never become hidden governance authorities.

---

# Frontend Philosophy

Frontends are operating dashboards.

Business logic belongs in:

* contracts
* SDKs
* backend services
* indexers

Frontends should:

* visualize
* coordinate
* aggregate
* monitor
* orchestrate

Avoid embedding governance logic in frontend state.

---

# Backend Philosophy

Backends are:

* indexers
* aggregators
* orchestrators
* telemetry providers
* execution coordinators

Backends must not become centralized authorities.

---

# Operational Rule

All systems must remain:

* modular
* replaceable
* composable
* observable
* governable
* auditable
